            <div type="translation">
                <p>O Pantanassa, and all-[surpassing chaste lady and mother of the Lord, see the desire of my miserable] soul and become my intercessor in the hour of judgment that I may be spared the lot of [...Nikephoros] magistros, of the (family of the) Ischyrioi. (<ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>, 77)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Poor condition. Partially preserved. A cross with dots in the angles marks the beginning and the end of the text. At the end of the inscription there are two units of pseudo-Kufic design. Μεσίτης, ὅπως, ὑσχυρίων are misspelled. Accents and breathings with errors. The reconstruction of the inscription is based on the apse inscription of the Panagia church at Trikomo, Cyprus. According to the scholars, the murals of Trikomo's church are probably attributed to the same painting workshop as that of Asinou's church or had just the same donor.
</p>
            </div>
